\pard\plain{\cf1\f4\fs20\li216\ql\ri216\sa20\sb20 Select a bitmap that will be tiled across the background.\line }\par
\pard\plain{\b\cf5\f4\fs20\li216\ql\ri216\sa20\sb20 Check program on startup:}\par
\pard\plain{\cf1\f4\fs20\li216\ql\ri216\sa20\sb20 This option is on by default for each new project you start. With this option checked, the ebook that you create checks itself on startup. If you are emailing your ebooks and/or making them available for download through the web, there is always a chance the file can be corrupted on download or cut off giving you only part of your ebook. This alerts the recipient of your ebook that there is a problem and that the downloaded file has been damaged. If you are creating big ebooks to burn on a CD-ROM, having your ebook check itself is not needed and the option can be turned off.}\par
